# HubSpot E2E Test Suite Rules

## Critical Rules

- Use `test.describe.serial()` for phase-based suites; plain `test.describe()` for standalone validation specs
- Number phase spec files with two-digit prefix: `01-`, `02-`, `03-`; standalone specs need no prefix
- Always use `waitForCondition` (not `setTimeout`) to poll async workflow results; always provide `timeoutMs`, `intervalMs`, `description`
- Write Phase N output as JSON golden record to `e2e/phase{N}-*.json`; read in Phase N+1 via helper functions
- Register every created HubSpot object with `registerCompany`/`registerContact`/`registerDeal`; call `runCleanup()` in `afterAll` only when `CLEANUP_AFTER_PHASE1=1`
- Generate test data via `generatePhase1TestData(UNIQUE)` â€” never hardcode names/emails; always append `UNIQUE` suffix (`e2e-${Date.now()}-${random}`)
- Country must be `"Germany"` or `"Switzerland"` only; `original_country` must be ISO code (`DE`/`CH`); `status` must be empty on creation so WF 1007 sets `"Aktiv"`
- All 14 mandatory company fields must be present (see `COMPANY_MANDATORY_FIELDS` in `crm-schema.ts`)
- Phone numbers must be `+digits` only (no spaces, no dashes)
- Use `Math.round(x * 100) / 100` for all financial rounding; use tolerance `0.01` for float comparisons
- Swiss CHF PDF format uses apostrophe as thousands separator (`6'486.00`) â€” normalize before `parseFloat`
- Use `test.skip(condition, reason)` for eligibility checks (e.g., `billing_cycle` not upfront/end_of_campaign)
- Accumulate assertion failures into `failures[]` array and report all at end â€” never fail-fast in loop
- Calculator modules in `line-item-calc-qa/calculators/` must export typed functions matching `types.ts` interface; route via `calculate()` in `index.ts`
- HubDB numeric option columns (e.g. `count_of_targetings`) must be filtered client-side, not via API params
- `LINE_ITEM_IDS` env var (comma-separated) takes precedence over demo IDs; `DEAL_ID` resolves IDs via association API

## Examples

<example>
// VALID: Phase-based serial test with polling, registration, and golden record
test.describe.serial("Phase 1: CRM Setup", () => {
  const UNIQUE = `e2e-${Date.now()}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 8)}`;
  test.beforeAll(async () => { testData = await generatePhase1TestData(UNIQUE); });
  test("TC-P1-1: Company created, WF 1007 sets Aktiv", async () => {
    const props = { ...testData.company, status: "" };
    companyId = await createCompany(props);
    registerCompany(companyId);
    await waitForCondition(
      async () => (await getCompanyProperties(companyId, ["status"])).status === "Aktiv",
      { timeoutMs: 30_000, intervalMs: 2_000, description: "company.status === 'Aktiv'" },
    );
  });
  test.afterAll(async () => { if (process.env.CLEANUP_AFTER_PHASE1 === "1") await runCleanup(); });
});

// VALID: Standalone financial validation with tolerance and skip
test("Validate amounts for deal", async () => {
  const billingCycle = await getDealBillingCycle(dealId);
  if (!isDealEligible(billingCycle)) { test.skip(true, `billing_cycle="${billingCycle}" not eligible`); return; }
  const failures: string[] = [];
  const diff = Math.abs(dealNetTotal - invoiceNetSum);
  if (diff >= 0.01) failures.push(`net mismatch: ${dealNetTotal} vs ${invoiceNetSum}`);
  expect(failures, failures.join("\n")).toHaveLength(0);
});
</example>

